{color:#333333}modPHPMailer is a class that extends modMail to provide an implementation for the open source PHPMailer class.{color}

h3. {color:#000000}{*}What is modSwiftMailer?*{color}

{color:#333333}[modSwiftMailer |ADDON:modSwiftMailer]{color}{color:#333333}is a{color} {color:#333333}{+}3rd-party core add-on{+}{color} {color:#333333}by Mark Ernst that extends the{color} {color:#333333}[modMail |revolution20:modMail]{color}{color:#333333}functionality and provides a much more configurable implementation of the native modMail (in combination with PHPMailer) class. &amp;nbsp;modSwiftMailer is based on{color} {color:#333333}[Swift Mailer|http://swiftmailer.org/]{color} {color:#333333}which is an open-source library by Chris Corbyn.&amp;nbsp;{color}{color:#333333}Although the usage of modSwiftMailer is almost exactly the same as modPHPMailer in core functionality, it provides a couple of differences and advantages. Please refer to the modSwiftMailer documentation for more information, installation\- and usage instructions.{color}

{color:#333333}{*}Note:*{color} {color:#333333}If you want to use modSwiftMailer, please download it from the{color} {color:#333333}[MODX Extras repository|http://modx.com/extras/]{color} {color:#333333}in your browser or in your MODX{color} {color:#333333}[revolution20:Package Management]{color}{color:#333333}.{color}

h2. Usage

The following example is based on the +native+ modPHPMailer which comes with MODX Revolution.

Let&#39;s say we have an email template in the Chunk &#39;myEmailTemplate&#39;. We want to send it via mail to user@example.com, with the From address being &#39;me@example.org&#39;. We also want it to be an HTML email. Here&#39;s how we&#39;d do it:

{code}
