$modx-&gt;mail-&gt;address(&#39;to&#39;,&#39;marketing@modxcms.com&#39;);
$modx-&gt;mail-&gt;address(&#39;to&#39;,&#39;mom@home.com&#39;);
{code}

And finally, the example code above will send a message to our error.log if the mail isn&#39;t sent for some reason (usually a server misconfiguration).

h2. What if I want to use another email class?

Simple - just extend modMail with that class, then load your class via [getService|modX.getService]. You&#39;ll get all the modMail functionality, but you will have to provide the wrapper class (like modPHPMailer) to do so.

h2. See Also

* [MODx Services]
* [modX.getService]

{scrollbar}";}}}